Sellers should invest in social media channels outside Amazon and check that product descriptions in the local language are optimised for search on platform and on other search engines.

fields.name: La Redoute
fields.description: La Redoute was founded in 1875 and opened a selective marketplace in 2010. It is the number one fashion and home e-commerce platform in France, with more than 11 million registered customers. With presence in over 26 countries, La Redoute caters mainly to women aged 25-45.
fields.customer_demographics: 90% female customers, La Redoute caters mainly to women aged 25-45. 99% brand awareness in France.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Powerful and varied promotional tools include email newsletter, dedicated shop-in-shop, banners, and flash sales.
fields.product_details_upload_notes: La Redoute also work with the following integrators: Lengow, Tradebyte, Channel Advisor, Anatwine and Neteven
fields.ukti_terms: Try for free for the first three months (only pay commission on items you sell)
fields.local_bank_account_needed_notes: Any European bank account is ok.
fields.local_incorporation_needed_notes: Will work with any European-based company. For British sellers, the company registration number is needed.
fields.translation_application_process_notes: Terms & Conditions will need to be provided in French
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: French is not required for business or technical support, but Sellers are required to offer Customer Service support in French.
fields.shipping_tracking_required_notes: Sellers must despatch goods within 5 days after receiving an order and must use tracked delivery service and provide the tracking URL to La Redoute..
fields.local_return_address_required_notes: Sellers must offer a local return address or a prepayed return label if returns go back to the UK.
fields.dit_advisor_tip:
La Redoute has a very selective recruitment strategy and is a full price marketplace carrying 50% of its own brands and 50% external. UK merchants selling over €35k p.a. in France must register for VAT with
French tax authorities.

fields.name: NeweggBusiness
fields.description: NeweggBusiness is the leading destination for organizations to learn, search, buy, and manage all their information technology needs. We provide an extensive assortment of IT products, services, and solutions to businesses, government agencies, healthcare organizations, and educational institutions of all sizes. Take advantage of inventory and fulfillment solutions, which include consignment warehousing in the U.S., and shipping and returns management services. In addition, capitalize on low commission fees and work closely with your dedicated category manager to reach over 300,000 customers.
fields.customer_demographics:
- Small-to-Medium-Sized Businesses: 40%
- Small Office / Home Office (SOHO): 23%
- Large Business: 18%*
- Public Sector: 16%
- Nonprofit: 3%

*Includes non-IT retail outlets.
fields.marketing_merchandising: NeweggBusiness offers exposure opportunities on a variety of marketing and merchandising vehicles, such as home page and category page exposure as well as emails and more.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Required within 72 hours of receiving an order and subject to Newegg minimum performance. Or use "shipped by Newegg" and let it take care of order fulfilment and logistics.
fields.ukti_terms: Commission reduced from 12% to 11% (and down to 10% for merchants selling over $100k/month)
fields.dit_advisor_tip: NeweggBusiness provides a great opportunity to trade in the USA with fewer barriers. One key feature of Newegg  is that it acts as the "merchant of record", therefore you will have no liability regarding US sales tax. Don't forget to use American English where appropriate in your product listings.

fields.name: LaModa
fields.description:
LaModa is one of five online marketplaces owned and operated by Global Fashion Group. The other four are Dafiti (Latin America), Namshi (Persian Gulf region), Zalora (southeast Asia) and THE ICONIC in Australia and New Zealand. 
All Global Fashion Group's online marketplaces sell top international and local brands in fashion and beauty. LaModa covers Belarus, Kazakhstan, Russia and Ukraine. A variety of operating models (wholesale, consignment and drop-ship) are offered.
fields.customer_demographics: 70% of LaModa's male and female customers are concentrated in the 25-45 age group. They are younger than the average of Russian internet users. 70% of customers are female except in the sports category (65% of sports customers are male).
fields.marketing_merchandising:
LaModa's marketing support includes: on-site marketing banners, a mobile app, CRM/newsletters, social media, blogs, LaModa's in-house online magazine. It also offers TV advertising, display and affiliate advertising, paid advertising, in-house search engine marketing and search engine optimisation.

Pricing is available on request from the Global Fashion Group team.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip:
To sell on LaModa, Global Fashion Group will look for brands with a good level of international brand awareness, technical capability to integrate with the platform, and proven overseas fulfilment capability. A combination of these factors will guide the discussions that Global Fashion Group have with the brand. 
Brands need to establish a legal entity in Russia to receive payment in Russian roubles.

fields.name: Zalora
fields.description: Zalora is one of five online marketplaces owned and operated by Global Fashion Group. The other four are Dafiti (Latin America), Namshi (Persian Gulf region), LaModa (Russia and the former CIS states) and THE ICONIC in Australia and New Zealand. All Global Fashion Group's online marketplaces sell top international and local brands in fashion and beauty. Zalora covers 6 markets in South East Asia. A variety of operating models (wholesale, consignment and drop-ship) are offered.
fields.customer_demographics: Fashion forward and fashion conscious male and female customers aged 20-40. Specific insights will vary across markets according to what retail channels already exist, the brands currently available, and general income levels.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
Zalora’s marketing support includes: on-site marketing banners, a mobile app, CRM/newsletters, social media, blogs, Zalora's in-house online magazine, TV advertising, display and affiliate advertising, paid advertising, in-house search engine marketing and search engine optimisation.

Pricing is available on request from the Global Fashion Group team.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: To sell on Zalora, Global Fashion Group will look for brands with a good level of international brand awareness, technical capability to integrate with the platform, and proven overseas fulfilment capability. A combination of these factors will guide the discussions that Global Fashion Group have with the brand.

fields.name: Newegg
fields.description: Newegg is the number one online marketplace for everything tech in the US. From consumer electronics to home automation to car electronics, you can sell your products to over 30 million interested customers. Streamline your business by leveraging 'Shipped by Newegg' fulfilment solutions: you can put consignment stock in the US, which Newegg will pick, pack, and dispatch for you. Capitalise on the low commission fees and drive effective marketing and merchandising campaigns by co-ordinating with Newegg's dedicated category and merchandising team.
fields.customer_demographics: Newegg's customers are 63% male and 37% female. 51% of Newegg customers earn more than USD 60,000, and 22% earn more than USD 100,000. Newegg has more than 2.3 million social media fans across 9 platforms and more than 3 million customer product reviews.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Newegg offers exposure opportunities on a variety of marketing and merchandising vehicles, such as home page and category page exposure, as well as segmented email blasts. An enhanced product listing (A+ content optimisation) is available for $60 USD per SKU. All sellers have a dedicated category manager and merchandiser.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Required within 72 hours of receiving an order and subject to Newegg minimum performance. Or use "shipped by Newegg" and let it take care of order fulfilment and logistics.
fields.ukti_terms: Commission reduced from 12% to 11% (and down to 10% for merchants selling over $100k/month)
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Newegg provides a great opportunity to trade in the USA with fewer barriers. One key feature of Newegg  is that it acts as the "merchant of record", therefore you will have no liability regarding US sales tax. Don't forget to use American English where appropriate in your product listings.

fields.name: Otto
fields.description: From its early beginnings as a catalogue business, in 2006 Otto expanded to include an online marketplace as well. The success of the business is based on best-in-class logistics and customer support, with specific expertise in fashion, consumer electronics and home furnishing.
fields.customer_support_hours: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week
fields.seller_support_hours: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week
fields.customer_demographics: Otto has 9 million active customers, mainly aged 25-55, 62% of whom are married women with above average income. The Otto Group reaches 45% of all German households in urban, semi-urban and rural locations through its catalogue and online markeplace businesses.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
A range of advertising and communications services are available, including special on-site advertising formats (banners), social media, a customer newsletter and branded online areas.

Extra fees may apply depending on the services required, and are negotiated direct between the merchant and Otto.
fields.ukti_terms: The 10,000 Euro fee that normally applies is waived for UK merchants that Otto agrees terms with
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Sellers will require a minimum of 100 products, experience with XML files for technical integration, previous online marketplace or e-shop experience, and will also need to translate their content into German. These criteria are non-negotiable.

fields.name: Xiu
fields.description:
Xiu.com is a Chinese cross-border online retailer with 12 million registered users. Founded in March 2008, Xiu.com sells mid-to-high range and luxury products including apparel (30%), shoes (20%), bags (20%), beauty (10%), accessories (10%), jewellery and watches (8%), and home (2%).
Xiu.com represents a low-cost entry to the Chinese market, offering a drop-ship model for selected UK partner brands.
Xiu.com will work with selected brands taking information via API link. Xiu.com will agree pricing with the brands and offer the products to Xiu.com customers.
fields.customer_support_hours: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week
fields.customer_demographics: Customers are mostly aged 25 to 45, and 55% are female. 70% of Xiu's customers living in the biggest Chinese cities (tiers one and two) and 30% live in tier three and tier four cities.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Xiu.com is willing to handle your marketing budget if you commit to them exclusively and agree not to sell on other platforms. Brands are advised to reinvest 30% of turnover in their marketing. Without exclusivity, Xiu.com will offer basic promotion on the site for free.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Deliver direct to the consumer in China
fields.commission_notes: There is no commission. Brands agree a price with Xiu.com
fields.ukti_terms: This is a drop-ship model with zero "onboarding" fees. Brands need to individually negotiate prices with Xiu.com team.
fields.translation_product_content_notes: Carried out by Xiu
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: Carried out by Xiu
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Building brand awareness in China across multiple consumer touchpoints, both online and offline, in the UK and China, is the only way to successfully enter the Chinese market. Brands must be committed to a marketing budget to make the most of this opportunity.

fields.name: VIP.com
fields.description:
Launched in Sep 2014, VIP Global is an independent channel on VIP.com selling only foreign brands. The overall VIP.com business is ranked third in terms of turnover which reached USD 6.2 billion for 2015. VIP has 19.7 million daily unique visitors and 200 million registered users.
This is a multi-product platform with key categories of apparel, home, handbags, shoes, cosmetics and beauty, mother and baby products, toys and food and drink.
VIP has an office in London that can liaise with UK companies on a day-to-day basis, during UK business hours.

VIP will buy the products or operate with consignment which is a matter of individual commercial negotiations between brands and the VIP buying teams.
fields.customer_demographics: 75% of registered users are female and aged 18 to 45 years. 80% of all sales on VIP are carried out on mobile devices.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Pricing is set by agreement between VIP and partner brands. VIP sells both in-season and off-season products. Brands can leverage VIP's site traffic by paid-for marketing.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Bulk delivery to nominated carrier with marketplace fulfilling to customer
fields.ukti_terms: This is either a wholesale model or a consignment model (fashion) with zero "onboarding" fees. Prices are negotiated with brands individually.
fields.translation_product_content_notes: VIP will carry out the translation
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: VIP will carry out the translation
fields.dit_advisor_tip: VIP will be more interested in brands with greater the brand recognition in China. Brands should consider registering their trademarks before expanding into China.

fields.name: Shangpin
fields.description:
Shangpin was established in 2010 as one of the leading luxury and fashion online platforms in China, and offers over 1,400 brands. It provides access to China’s mid-to-high end fashion consumers, extending into the luxury market. Shangpin is a premium online fashion retailer.
In 2014, as the exclusive online partner of Arcadia Group in China, Shangpin introduced Topshop/Topman into the country. Shangpin has 32 million registered users, and offers a simple drop-ship model for UK brands.
fields.customer_support_hours: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week
fields.customer_demographics: Customers demographics are 60% women and 40% men. The customer base is comprised of fashion-conscious buyers from 16 years and up. The average basket size is USD 200, and Shangpin has repeat purchase rates of 80%.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Shangpin has 10 photographic teams for imagery, and it works with a group of celebrities and key opinion leaders (KOLs) as well as running general marketing and promotions for brands. Alongside this marketing offered by Shangpin, brands should set aside about 20% of projected annual turnover for their own additional marketing budget.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: UK sellers deliver directly to the home address of Chinese consumers
fields.commission_notes: This is a drop ship model where prices are pre-agreed
fields.ukti_terms: This is a drop-ship model with zero onboarding fees. Prices are individually negotiated between Shangpin and the brand.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Brands should register their trademarks prior to launching into the Chinese market. To succeed in China, promotion and brand awareness are crucial, and must be budgeted for. The greater the brand awareness in China, the more likely that Shangpin will work with a brand.

fields.name: JD Worldwide
fields.description: JD Worldwide has 35% of China's B2C e-commerce market and is a cross-border e-commerce site offering products from overseas. It has 188 million annual active customers (those who have shopped at least once in the previous 12 months). They have two business models, one is the seller's own store, where a brand will have their own shop and sell directly to consumers, and the other model involves wholesale purchases by JD from the brands. JD have a huge logistics infrstructure which sellers can utilise for both warehousing and delivery.
fields.customer_support_hours: 24 hours, 7 days a week; also through an app
fields.customer_demographics: JD.com's 188 million registered users are 68% male, 32% female. 80% of shoppers are aged 18-45, and 65% have university degrees.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Brands need to engage the services of a third party, trusted partner to run the core functions of the store. Translations, imagery, optimised descriptions, customer service and return handling. Costs for these services are negotiable. A marketing budget must be set aside to encourage greater brand engagement as it's essential for brands to raise awareness in China.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Logistics provided by seller's third party partner
fields.ukti_terms: $1000 annual fee waived for UK companies for the first year
fields.local_bank_account_needed_notes: USD company bank account needed to receive payment
fields.translation_product_content_notes: To be brovided by local partner
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: To be provided by local partner
fields.deposit_notes: Deposit is USD 10,000 to 15,000 depending on certain metrics
fields.dit_advisor_tip: JD.com can integrate with a WeChat store which can offer a powerful online combination for UK brands. A verified Wechat service account can have ecommerce functionality and incorporates various marketing tools.

fields.name: Allegro
fields.description: Allegro is one of the most popular online shopping destinations in Poland. Over 18 million visitors shop the site monthly, contributing to the sale of over 850,000 items on the platform every day. The most notable product categories include fashion, electronics, home and garden and kids and baby. Allegro has developed a special channel called Brand Zone, which is available to brand owners and official distribution partners across all product categories.
fields.customer_support_hours: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week
fields.seller_support_hours: Email: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. Telephone 8.00am to 5.00pm CET
fields.customer_demographics: Allegro's customers are 53% female and 47% male. Of these, 26% are 15-24 years old, 34% are 25-34 years old, and 34% are 35-49 years old. 39% live in cities of up to 200,000 residents.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Allegro's ads system has the following promotional options: featuring, highlighting, bolding, promotion on product category page, daily deals, and brand zone. Ad placements include being showcased on the main page and landing pages.
fields.product_details_upload_notes: Integrators include: Pentagon and Lengow (coming soon)
fields.ukti_terms: Special marketing package worth up to £1000 for qualifying sellers
fields.dit_advisor_tip: To sell successfully on Allegro, you will need to be able to offer customer services in Polish. To translate your product listings accurately, make sure you use a native speaker, and avoid machine translation.

fields.name: Spartoo
fields.description: Spartoo.co.uk is an ecommerce website specialising in shoes and clothing. Based in Grenoble, France, it was created in 2009 as part of the company Spartoo.com. Spartoo offers first-line customer service in 12 different languages and operates in 30 European countries. Spartoo works with sellers through a standard marketplace drop-ship model, allowing it to sell into all the countries where it has a presence.
fields.customer_demographics: Spartoo's core demographic is women aged 30 to 40.
fields.marketing_merchandising: No merchandising, 12 million spent on online marketing per year. As with all marketplaces, you can make your products more visible by writing good product titles, making sure product descriptions are detailed, and adding multiple high-quality images to show items from several angles and zoom in for detail.
fields.ukti_terms: Try for free for the first 3 months (only pay commission on items you sell)
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Spartoo will only work with sellers who can offer a minimum of 250 SKUs. Although a relatively small player in the UK, Spartoo is a household name in France and across much of Europe. Spartoo offers a great one-stop solution to access Europe’s huge online fashion market.

fields.name: FlipKart
fields.description: Flipkart is India's largest ecommerce marketplace, with over 65% market share in major categories. Key product categories include electronics, fashion, kids and baby, homeware, and sports and fitness. UK brands must partner with an Indian aggregator to sell on the platform (Flipkart can make the introduction). This aggregator acts as the registered seller and manages the seller's operations in India, including listings, managing inventory, returns, customer service, and shipping and customs clearance.
fields.customer_support_hours: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week
fields.seller_support_hours: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week
fields.customer_demographics: Flipkart caters to India's biggest cities (tier 1, 2 and 3 cities). The majority of online shoppers are under 35.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Flipkart will support merchandising for brands who meet product selection and expected pricing benchmarks. Flipkart has various channels to promote brands directly on the platform and through affiliates. It also offers special merchandising packages on a paid basis.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Sellers work with an Indian aggregator. The aggregator collects parcel from the UK seller location and delivers to the customer
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.shipping_tracking_required_notes: Flipkart's aggregator will collect the items from the seller's location and handle delivery.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Indian consumers are very price-conscious and having the right pricing strategy can be the difference between success and failure in India. The costs to sell are significant: when you factor-in customs duties, Flipkart's commission, the aggregator's margin, and local VAT, it can add up to between 25% and 80% of your margin.

fields.name: Trade Me
fields.description: Trade Me is New Zealand's most popular website and largest digital platform. In fact, 75% of all domestic web traffic in New Zealand goes to Trade Me. Trade Me offers a strong product and brand demand, in the opposite season to the Northern hemisphere, and sells everything from apparel to sports gear to car parts. Top-selling categories include fashion, computers and electronics, toys and hobbies, home and living, baby, and sports. Brands and retailers are invited to join the platform based on likelihood of their success in market and category demand.
fields.customer_support_hours: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week
fields.seller_support_hours: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week
fields.customer_demographics: Because 85% of the population of New Zealand hold a Trade Me account, the platform reaches a very broad demographic spread.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
For brands with good commercial opportunity Trade Me offers:

1. Display advertising across the website site

2. "Solus" email marketing

3. Newsletter inclusion (1.6 million subscribers)

4. Social media push (100,000 Facebook followers, 17,000 Twitter followers)

Trade Me may also consider external marketing for the right brand.
fields.product_details_upload_notes: Integrators include: Channel Advisor, Black Pepper
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Trade Me can make recommendations on logistics partners
fields.ukti_terms: 15% reduction in commission from 9.85% gross (including payment fees) to 8.37%
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Trade Me wants to work with sellers who have strong ecommerce experience. As a general guideline you should be generating approximately £125,000 to 200,000 a year on existing marketplaces.

fields.name: Cdiscount
fields.description:
With 7.7 million active users and 11 million unique visitors to the site every month, Cdiscount is an essential marketplace in France. It offers an extensive range of products in over 40 different categories, such as apparel, shoes and accessories, consumer electronics, jewellery, entertainment, sports equipment, games and toys, and food & drink. 
Cdiscount also operates its own fulfillment service, making this marketplace a great option for any retailer looking to expand their business in the French market. It offers best-in-class delivery options, with a network of 18,500 pickup points.
fields.customer_support_hours: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week
fields.seller_support_hours: Online and email: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. Telephone: 8.30am to 9pm (GMT +1)
fields.customer_demographics: Because Cdiscount lists such a wide range of items, the customer demographics are very broad.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Cdiscount's "pole position program" is one of several ways sellers can increase their visibility on the marketplace. It can help sellers to increase traffic, strengthen customer loyalty and receive more product reviews.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Seller responsible for shipping, unless using CLogistique, which is available at extra cost
fields.ukti_terms: Try for free for the first 3 months (only pay commission on items you sell). This is valid during 2016 for all new registrations and subject to acceptance by Cdiscount.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Cdiscount has been around since 1998 and is a household name among French consumers. It is particularly well-known for electronics and tech products, and is popular with tech-savvy shoppers looking for good prices.

fields.name: Amazon China
fields.description: Amazon provides sellers of all sizes with an international sales channel to a ready-made audience of many consumers. There are no upfront costs of creating a website or setting up a physical store. Sellers can elect to use 'Fulfilment by Amazon' where their products are stored in Amazon's warehouse and Amazon packs and delivers the orders to customers, provides customer service and handles returns. The safe payments infrastructure provided by Amazon helps minimise risk for sellers who want to begin selling overseas.
fields.customer_support_hours: Business hours (China), 8am to 6pm, Mon to Sun
fields.seller_support_hours: Business hours (China), 8am to 6pm, Mon to Sun
fields.customer_demographics: Amazon.cn covers a broad demographic of men and women, and of all ages.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Amazon marketing services offer a range of services to sellers at extra cost, including keyword-targeted advertising, headline search advertising and product display advertising.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.deposit_notes: Legal requirement in China. Varies by category.
fields.dit_advisor_tip:
Sellers will require the services of a third party company to provide the legal and financial entity in China necessary to trade on Amazon China. 
Sellers must arrange with their chosen service provider to receive payment in Renminbi and convert to Sterling, or ask the service provider to convert Renminbi to Sterling.
Amazon China works with a group of partner service providers and these companies can also provide "final-mile delivery" and returns services.

fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.

fields.dit_advisor_tip: Sellers can also use amazon.ca to sell on amazon.com in the US and amazon.ca in Canada without paying an extra membership fee.

fields.name: Etsy
fields.description: Etsy is a global marketplace connecting buyers and sellers in almost every country in the world, both online and offline, to make, sell and buy unique goods. Etsy offers support to emerging and established creative companies. It has 26 million buyers and 1.7 million registered sellers, worldwide. The heart of Etsy is their global community of sellers. There are numerous channels of support for sellers.
fields.customer_support_hours: Online help: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week
fields.seller_support_hours: Online help: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week
fields.customer_demographics: Etsy's global audience consists of people of all ages. They are mainly looking for new ideas and gifts.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Etsy believes advertisements should help sellers grow their businesses and contribute to the overall member experience. Etsy offers multiple advertising channels to sellers to promote their listings. Etsy's advertising policy explains sellers' rights and responsibilities when using Etsy’s advertising services.
fields.commission_notes: 3.5%, plus 4% plus GBP 0.20 for payment processing
fields.ukti_terms: Approved UK companies that are new to Etsy will receive 20 free listings.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: The most popular products on Etsy are clothing and accessories, jewellery, craft supplies and tools, weddings, entertainment, home and living, kids and baby, and vintage.

fields.name: Westwing
fields.description:
Westwing is a shoppable online magazine and marketplace. It provides the latest reviews and content about products, while enabling consumers to buy them from the platform.
In each country that it operates in, Westwing run five online marketing campaigns per day. Every campaign lasts around four to six days.
fields.customer_demographics: 95% of Westwing's customers are female and aged 25-60 years. Over 50% have a monthly income of EUR 3,000. In Germany, the average Westwing consumer spends more than EUR 1,700 on interior furnishings each year, which is twice the German national average. Westwing customers are passionate about decorations and home furnishings, and avidly follow social media and digital platfoms such as Pinterest, Instagram and Snapchat.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Specific marketing terms can be agreed between the seller and e-marketplace. This normally takes the form of an additional discount on the seller list price to pay for marketing activities that Westwing manages on its own communications channels and via other partners. Alternatively sellers can invest their own marketing budgets to support sell-through of products on the platform. Westwing is active on multiple social media channels (Facebook, YouTube, Instagram, Snapchat), and partners with local bloggers in each market to promote listed products to its audiences.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.translation_product_content_notes: Carried out by Westwing
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Westwing operates a wholesale model in a wide range of markets, with a particular focus on major European countries. UK sellers can deliver to a specified Westwing distribution centre in each of the European countries covered by the platform, but need to use their own local distributors if selling through Westwing to customers in Russia or Brazil.

fields.name: eBay
fields.description: eBay connect sellers to 164 million buyers worldwide, including 22 million active users in the UK. 80% of products sold on the platform are new, and 86% sold at fixed price rather than auction. 58% of eBay's sales are cross-border trade.
fields.customer_demographics: Because eBay lists such a wide range of items, the customer demographics are very broad.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Marketing on eBay is supported with a suite of tools including eBay shops (branded stores or micro-sites), seller hub and promote your listings to help you drive traffic and sales.
fields.ukti_terms: For entry level marketplace sellers, eBay is waiving the Shop subscription fee for 3 months when subscribing to an eBay Basic Shop (worth £17.38 per month). For any UK seller with current marketplace sales above $500,000 (currently c £410,000) on any marketplace, eBay is offering a free Anchor Store for 6 months (worth £217.38 per month).
fields.fee_per_listing_notes: eBay offers a choice of options. Listing fees are shown on the web site, and charged on sale.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: The eBay Global Shipping Programme makes international postage as simple as selling to someone in the UK. Sellers simply post items to a UK shipping centre, and eBay takes care of customs clearance, tracking and all the rest. You don’t have to pay anything extra - just the cost of posting the item to the UK shipping centre.

fields.name: Ctrip
fields.description: Founded in 1999 and listed on Nasdaq in 2003, Ctrip is the largest online provider of travel services in China including accommodation reservation, transportation, ticketing, package tours and corporate travel management. Ctrip has had more than 1 billion downloads of its mobile application and has 250 million registered users. Ctrip Global Shopping, is a pioneering offline-to-online (O2O) shopping programme launched in 2014. Ctrip has developed an online shopping marketplace directed at its 250 million members, offering a wide variety of international products, services and gift cards. Ctrip is looking to build relationships with retailers who are looking to attract Chinese overseas travellers.
fields.customer_demographics: Ctrip's customers tend to be international travellers - predominantly high net-worth individuals. Of these, 61.8% are female and 38.2% are male; 88% are aged 20 to 40 years.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Ctrip employs a wide variety of marketing initiatives to promote products. These include product listing destination recommendations, SMS/electronic direct mail promotions, geo-location push messaging, banner advertising and WeChat promotions.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: UK sellers to deliver direct to the consumer, with local hotel, airport or overseas address
fields.ukti_terms: A special reduced commission rate will be 5% for qualifying companies.
fields.translation_application_process_notes: Ctrip can assist for a fee
fields.translation_product_content_notes: Ctrip can assist for a fee
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: Provided by Ctrip
fields.dit_advisor_tip: A recent survey found that almost 60% of Chinese consumers buy only from apparel brands they are familiar with. Grabbing the attention of Chinese tourists when visiting the UK is a good place to start to build that familiarity.

fields.name: Mercado Libre
fields.description: Mercado Libre is the top ecommerce retailer in Latin America, operating in 18 countries. Mercado Libre is in the top 50 most-visited sites in the world (8th most-visited retail site in the world). It receives 4,000 searches per second, and has 24 million buyers and 8 million sellers.
fields.customer_demographics: Mercado Libre has a broad demographic coverage due to the wide range of categories sold. Its customers are male and female across all ages and social levels.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Mercado Libre offers special promotion dates (such as Cyber Monday, Black Friday, hot sales, fashion week and electronics week), as well as email and Facebook marketing, TV, radio and internet ads, and branding campaigns.
fields.ukti_terms: Standard commission is 10% (Colombia), 12% (Chile) and 16% (Mexico), across all categories. Commission reduced by 1% (Colombia, Chile) and 2% (Mexico) for DIT-referred sellers.
fields.local_bank_account_needed_notes: Mercado Libre transfers the money to the bank account where the seller is located.
fields.translation_application_process_notes: The terms and conditions and contract will be in English.
fields.translation_product_content_notes: A Spanish speaker is needed to manage the account for customer service, pre- and post-sale, questions and claims
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: Mercado Libre plans to add seller support in English.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: MercadoShops is a feature on Mercado Libre that allows brands to set up their own personalised online store within the website. This is a good option to boost brand awareness, and creates a dedicated destination for your products on Mercado Libre.

fields.name: Amazon India
fields.description:
Amazon provides sellers of all sizes with an international sales channel to a ready-made audience of many consumers. There are no upfront costs of creating a website or setting up a physical store. Sellers can elect to use 'Fulfilment by Amazon' where their products are stored in Amazon's warehouse and Amazon packs and delivers the orders to customers, provides customer service and handles returns. The safe payments infrastructure provided by Amazon helps minimise risk for sellers who want to begin selling overseas. 
In India, Amazon only operates a wholesale-only model.
fields.customer_demographics: Amazon.in covers a broad demographic of men and women, and of all ages.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Amazon marketing services offer a range of services to sellers at extra cost, including keyword-targeted advertising, headline search advertising and product display advertising.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip:
In order to sell on Amazon India, sellers must identify a third party service provider to represent them in India. This company will provide the legal and financial entity for Amazon to trade with.

Sellers should invest in social media channels outside Amazon and check that product descriptions in the local language are optimised for search on platform and on other search engines.

fields.name: Royal Mail Tmall Store
fields.description:
Tmall is a business-to-consumer (B2C) platform that has over 400 million registered members and receives over 100 million unique visitors per day. Tmall is part of the Alibaba Group.
Recently, Tmall has developed Tmall Global, a service that enables brands from outside China to sell on its online marketplace. The Royal Mail store on Tmall Global offers UK companies a route to sell to consumers in China that combines low entry cost, presence on the Royal Mail-branded domain alongside other UK brands. It also carries the guarantee of protection from exchange rate movement.
fields.customer_demographics: Tmall demand is marginally higher in females, and the dominant age group is 25-45.
fields.marketing_merchandising: A range of marketing services exists, and can be tailored to budgets and related requirements.
fields.ukti_terms: £1,500 to register five products on T-mall and 6 months reduced account service fee of £100 per month once merchant starts trading. This offer is valid until 31st March 2017.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: An easy, low-cost and rapid way for sellers to establish a presence on an online marketplace in China. A budget to create a social media presence on digital channels outside Tmall Global must be part of your export plan.

fields.name: Kaola
fields.description: Kaola.com is a cross-border ecommerce platform selling "western" brands, and forms part of the huge NetEase Corporation. With access to over 840 million subscribers of multiple NetEase services, Kaola.com offers an opportunity for UK brands to showcase their products across a huge number of online forums, portals and marketing channels. Kaola offers 3 business models of wholesale buying, online marketplace for sellers and API interconnection for UK ecommerce.
fields.customer_support_hours: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. Also through an app
fields.seller_support_hours: 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. Also through an app
fields.customer_demographics: The main products demanded by Kaola shoppers are baby formula and baby products, packaged foods and nutrition products, cosmetics, household and personal care products, apparel and accessories, small consumer electronic products.
fields.marketing_merchandising: If brands offer exclusivity, Kaola will help with marketing. Brand awareness is essential for success in China,so non-exclusive brands will need to set aside a budget for marketing and brand building.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: Third party store management company to arrange
fields.ukti_terms: $1000 annual fee waived for UK companies for the first year
fields.translation_product_content_notes: Provided by brand's third party partner
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: Provided by brand's third party partner
fields.dit_advisor_tip: When considering China as a market, you must register your trademark and set aside about 20% of projected turnover to a very well-targeted marketing campaign. To run the store successfully on Kaola, you will need the services of a third party to handle translations, customer service, returns and imagery.

fields.name: THE ICONIC
fields.description:
THE ICONIC covers Australia and New Zealand and is one of five online marketplaces owned and operated by Global Fashion Group. The other four are Dafiti (Latin America), Namshi (Persian Gulf region), LaModa (Russia and the former CIS states) and Zalora (southeast Asia). All Global Fashion Group's online marketplaces sell top international and local brands in fashion and beauty. A variety of operating models (wholesale, consignment and drop-ship) are offered.
THE ICONIC launches over 200 new products each day and offers a wide range of delivery options to suit the needs of its community.
fields.customer_demographics: Customers of THE ICONIC are 75% female. Young female professionals make up the marketplace's core consumers. However, 50% of female customers also shop for male products as gifts. THE ICONIC has 90% brand awareness among its core target audience.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
Marketing and communications products on offer include: shop-in-shop or branded landing page, on-site marketing banners, mobile app, CRM/newsletters, social media, blogs, in-house magazine, display and affiliate advertising, paid advertising, in-house search engine marketing and search engine optimisation.

THE ICONIC can provide a tailored package depending on the marketing agreement with your brand.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip: To sell on THE ICONIC, Global Fashion Group will look for brands with a good level of international brand awareness, technical capability to integrate with the platform, and proven overseas fulfilment capability. A combination of these factors will guide the discussions that Global Fashion Group have with the brand.

fields.name: Rakuten
fields.description: Rakuten is the fourth largest e-marketplace in the world, and is the leading platform in Japan. The consumer experience is similar to a 'shopping mall' environment, and sellers can develop their own brand presence inside the marketplace using four different levels of plan. Rakuten has recently launched a new service to enable UK companies to sell directly to Japanese consumers.
fields.customer_demographics: Rakuten is used by men and women of all ages.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
There are four levels of store presentation that a seller can buy:

- Entry Plan (JPY 19,500)

- Lite Plan (JPY 39,800)

- Standard Plan (JPY 50,000)

- Mega-Shop Plan (JPY 100,000)

Sellers can also buy performance marketing packages for search and/or banner advertising.
fields.ukti_terms: No current offer.
fields.dit_advisor_tip:
Sellers will require the services of a third party company to provide the legal and financial entity in Japan necessary to trade on Rakuten. 
Sellers must arrange with their chosen service provider to receive payment in Japanese Yen and convert to Sterling, or ask the service provider to convert Japanese Yen to Sterling.
Rakuten works with a group of partner service providers such as Brangista, Café 24, EC Robo, I-Order and TransCosmos. These companies can also provide final mile delivery and returns services.

fields.name: Privalia
fields.description:
Privalia is a flash sales and buy by category platform for fashion brands and retailers. It organises short, single-category campaigns lasting between 3 and 5 days to which registered members are invited to shop via an email message and mobile alerts.

Sellers have an easy and profitable way of selling the remaining items in their inventory and customers obtain brand-name products at significantly lower prices than those they would find in stores.
fields.customer_demographics: Privalia in Spain has 8.5 million registered users and Privalia in Italy has 7.6 million registered users. 70% of them are women aged between 30 and 45 years old. 60% are medium to medium-high social status and earn between EUR 1,200 to 2,500 a month. A third of users have children and buy for the whole family. This buying behaviour applies to both Spain and Italy.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
Best price and discount products participate in high-profile curated category events that Privalia manage.

Sellers can also organise specific branded events if the goods they offer can generate EUR 15,000 sales across 2 days of activity.
fields.ukti_terms: DIT introduced brands can benefit from 2% lower commission fees (13% for brands and 11% for retailers)
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Sellers must have a minimum of 300 Stock Keeping Units (SKUs), capability to deliver to Spain or Italy in 5 business days, and Italian and Spanish language customer service to communicate with consumers.

fields.name: British Pavilion on 1688.com
fields.description:
Part of the Alibaba Group, 1688.com is the largest online B2B e-commerce marketplace in China, with over 120 million registered business users and a transaction value of approximately RMB 250 billion. 
1688.com is a seller marketplace using a local wholesale model, with stock held in warehouses in China. The British Food and Drink Pavilion is a platform on 1688.com, established to sell the best of British Food & Drink to the most reputable distributors across China. The British food and beverage store is run by LNP China and global food and drink brands, and is called 'The British Pavilion'.
fields.customer_demographics:
Buyers are wholesale distributors and retailers located mainly in Beijing, Shanghai, Qingdao, Dalian, Chongqing and Guangzhou. The buyers have included mid-sized supermarket chains and owners of reputable online e-commerce stores in China.

Chinese distributors purchasing imported products from 1688.com will be targeting the rising middle class in China. British brands are attractive as they satisfy customer requirements for quality, heritage, health and innovation.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Brand awareness and brand building are essential parts of a successful strategy in China. An initial spend of 20% of projected annual turnover is considered a normal requirement.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: The British Pavilion will deal with logistics starting from a UK consolidation point and offering brand owners single pallet delivery options. Stock is then held in China ready for sale.
fields.commission_notes: Commission is variable depending on sales volume.
fields.ukti_terms: This is a wholesale model and prices are negotiated directly with LNP China. The British Pavilion carries GREAT branding.
fields.translation_product_content_notes: This will be done by LNP China
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: This will be done by LNP China
fields.dit_advisor_tip: All products need to be fully compliant with Chinese food regulations. The British Pavilion charges upfront fees for import research reports, pricing, product registrations, translation and Chinese labelling. Payment terms are 30 days after sale in China.

fields.name: Jack Russell Emporium on JD.com
fields.description: JD.com is the second largest business-to-consumer (B2C) ecommerce site in China, with 188 million active users. Jack Russell Emporium provides a one-stop, total solution to access the Chinese market from the UK through the JD Worldwide platform. Jack Russell Emporium offers a carefully curated selection of British premium and high street brands to aspirational Chinese customers. Products offered on JD.com are in fashion, health and beauty, and homeware.
fields.customer_demographics: Jack Russell Emporium caters for aspirational middle-class shoppers. They are 70% male, with an average age of 38, while 30% are female with an average age of 37. In total, 69% of customers are from China's biggest cities (tier one and tier two cities) and 23% from tier 3 cities and 8% spread across tier 4 and tier 5 cities.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
Marketing through Jack Russell Emporium uses targeted social media and in-channel promotion and includes promotional visibility on platform of 30 million visits per day. Vendor brands can feature in Emporium marketing. Jack Russell Emporium also has it's own production house for creating campaigns.
Jack Russell Emporium has its own Chinese UK-based staff to refine brand message. The marketplace also enables access to over 50,000 key opinion leaders including TV and film celebrities, fashion magazines (such as Elle), bloggers (with over a million followers) and access to Chinese national newspapers.
fields.logistics_structure_notes: UK seller delivers to UK hub. Jack Russell Emporium take care of the rest
fields.ukti_terms: This is a cross-border sales model: brands need to agree a wholesale price with the Jack Russell Emporium team in London.
fields.translation_application_process_notes: JRE UK headquarter will handle the matter in English
fields.translation_product_content_notes: JRE UK headquarter will handle the matter in English
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: JRE partner will handle the matter locally
fields.registration_fees_notes: By negotiation with Jack Russell Emporium London team
fields.dit_advisor_tip: Brands should have a significant marketing budget to raise awareness among Chinese consumers. Wechat, live streaming, use of key opinion leaders, contact with Chinese students in UK should all be contemplated as part of a marketing strategy.

fields.name: SF Best
fields.description:
Launched in 2012, SF Best has both an e-commerce platform (sfbest.com) and almost 2000 physical stores across China, covering more than 60 first, second and third tier cities. The number of SF Best stores is expanding with the roll-out of its national franchise programme. 

SF Best's main focus is on imported food and drink from around the world. It is looking to expand the number of UK food and drink brands they buy, to offer to their 20 million registered users. The online marketplace will buy the products, requiring individual commercial negotiations between brands and the SF Best buying teams. 

SF Best is developing a large number of own-brand products and are interested in talking to original equipment manufacturers. SF Best would also like to talk to UK distributors of multiple food products.
Categories include snacks, frozen foods, drinks and beverages (such as milk, soft drinks).
fields.customer_support_hours: 24 hours, 7 days a week. Also through an app
fields.seller_support_hours: Business hours (China), 8am to 6pm, Mon to Sun
fields.customer_demographics: SF Best's core customers are middle class households (85%) and the rest upper middle class.90% of customers come from tier one, two and three cities.
fields.marketing_merchandising: SF Best would like UK brands to provide marketing material, samples and resources which SF Best can then push through their own marketing channels.
fields.product_details_upload_notes: SF Best team in China will ask for basic information and graphics from UK suppliers
fields.logistics_structure_notes: SF Best buy CIF from UK sellers
fields.ukti_terms: None currently available because this is a wholesale model.
fields.exclusivity_required_notes: Exclusivity is preferred but not compulsory
fields.translation_product_content_notes: Carried out by SF Best at their cost
fields.translation_seller_support_notes: Carried out by SF Best at their cost
fields.dit_advisor_tip: SF Best will only buy products which can legally be sold in China which require CFDA and CIQ approvals in place. For a product to be selected by SF Best it must be very price competitive bearing in mind that quality is also of prime importance. Trademark registration should be carried out as soon as possible.

.

By using Amazon's easy to use functionality, sellers can use their UK account to list products in Italy as well as France, Germany and Spain.

Sellers should invest in social media channels outside Amazon and check that product descriptions in the local language are optimised for search on platform and on other search engines.

fields.name: Dafiti
fields.description:
Dafiti is one of five online marketplaces owned and operated by Global Fashion Group. The other four are Namshi (Persian Gulf region), LaModa (Russia and the former CIS states), Zalora (southeast Asia) and THE ICONIC in Australia and New Zealand. 
All Global Fashion Group's online marketplaces sell top international and local brands in fashion and beauty. Dafiti covers Argentina, Brazil, Chile and Columbia and it offers a variety of operating models (wholesale, consignment and drop-ship).
fields.customer_demographics: Dafiti's customers are 40% male and 60% female, and are mainly aged 25 to 45.
fields.marketing_merchandising:
Marketing and communications products on offer include: shop-in-shop or branded landing page, on-site marketing banners, mobile app, CRM/newsletters, social media, blogs, in-house magazine, display and affiliate advertising, paid advertising, in-house search engine marketing and search engine optimisation.

Dafiti can provide a tailored package depending on the marketing agreement with your brand.

A combination of these factors will guide the discussions that Global Fashion Group have with your brand.

Sellers can also sell on amazon.com and amazon.ca without paying an extra membership fee.
Sellers should invest in social media channels outside Amazon and check that product descriptions in the local language are optimised for search on platform and on other search engines.
